Package org.oucs.oxpoints.exceptions

Contains various exceptions that are used in the OxPoints system.

See:
          Description

Exception Summary
CorruptDataException Is thrown when it is suspected that the data in OxPoints is corrupted.
CorruptTimeIndexException Is thrown when it is suspected the time index is corrupt.
EntityAlreadyExistsException Is thrown when an entity is added to the OxPoints model that already exists.
EntityClassNotFoundException Is thrown when the corresponding OxPointsEntity class for an ontology type could not be determined.
EntityDoesNotExistException Is thrown when an OxPointsEntity is accessed that does not exist in the model.
EntityPoolAmbiguousConfigurationException Is thrown if the OxPointsEntityPoolConfiguration can be used for the creation of an OxPointsEntityPool, but if it is ambiguous in some way.
EntityPoolInvalidConfigurationException Is thrown if an OxPointsEntityPoolConfiguration is invalid.
IllegalAnnotationException Is thrown if an OxPointsEntity class is using annotations wrongly.
NoTimeIndexSetException Is thrown when a time index is accessed in an OxPoints model that did not create one.
OxPointsException Provides a common base class for Exceptions within OxPoints.
OxPointsRuntimeException Bas class for any runtime exception in the OxPoints system.
QueryAlreadyPreparedException  
ResourceDoesNotExistException Is thrown when an RDF resource is accessed that does not exist.
UnsupportedFormatException Is thrown if an unsupported format is supplied.
 

Package org.oucs.oxpoints.exceptions Description

Contains various exceptions that are used in the OxPoints system.
